abstract.p:
The present invention relates to a method for facilitating the renewing of a digital identity document, the method comprising the following steps of:

- receiving (301) a request for renewing a digital identity document;

- checking (302) whether said digital identity document can be renewed;

- if the check result is positive, creating (303) an up-to-date validity-related data item to be associated with said digital identity document and to be inspected by a verifier when the validity of said digital identity document must be assessed;

- sending (304) said up-to-date validity-related data item to a device of a user of said digital identity document so that a validity-related data item previously associated with said digital identity document can be replaced by said up-to-date validity-related data item at the user's side.

description.p:
In a particular embodiment of the present invention, a method for facilitating the renewing of a digital identity document comprises the following steps of:


receiving a request for renewing a digital identity document;

checking whether the digital identity document can be renewed;

if the check result is positive, creating an up-to-date validity-related data item to be associated with the digital identity document and to be inspected by a verifier when the validity of said digital identity document must be assessed;

sending the up-to-date validity-related data item to a device of a user of the digital identity document so that a validity-related data item previously associated with the digital identity document can be replaced by the up-to-date validity-related data item at the user's side.

In a particular embodiment of the present invention, the method further comprises:


calculating a derived value of the up-to-date validity-related data item by using a derivation function;

signing said derived value and derived values of other data components of the digital identity document as a signed data object;

sending the signed data object to the user.

The accompanying drawings, which are incorporated in and constitute a part of this description, illustrate embodiments consistent with the invention and, together with the description, serve to explain the principles of the invention.


Fig. 1 illustrates a system for facilitating the renewing of digital identity documents in accordance with an embodiment of the present invention;

Fig. 2 represents a hardware configuration of a digital identity document renewal system of practicing the principles of the present invention in accordance with an embodiment of the present invention;

Fig. 3 illustrates a flowchart of a method for facilitating the renewing of digital identity documents in accordance with an embodiment of the present invention.

claim.claim-text:
A method for facilitating the renewing of a digital identity document, the method comprising the following steps of:
- receiving (301) a request for renewing a digital identity document;
- checking (302) whether said digital identity document can be renewed;
- if the check result is positive, creating (303) an up-to-date validity-related data item to be associated with said digital identity document and to be inspected by a verifier when the validity of said digital identity document must be assessed;
- sending (304) said up-to-date validity-related data item to a device of a user of said digital identity document so that a validity-related data item previously associated with said digital identity document can be replaced by said up-to-date validity-related data item at the user's side.

A method according to any of claims 10-12, wherein the method further comprises:
- calculating a derived value of the up-to-date validity-related data item by using a derivation function;
- signing the calculated derived value and derived values of other data components of the digital identity document as a signed data object;
- sending said signed data object to the user.
